      • parseREFERENCE

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,StarlingReference> parseREFERENCE(java.lang.String s)
        Parse REFERENCE element for bibliographic references.

        Example 1 :
        "VEWT 293, ЭСТЯ 5, 118, Лексика 414-415."

        Example 2 :
        "VEWT 107, 110; EDT 404, 412. Turk. > MMong. (HY 20) čix, WMong. čig, Khalkha čig, Ord. čīg 'bamboo screen'. The Nogh. form may be a compound; for the second part cf. *bɨńan."

        Specified by:
        parseREFERENCE in interface StarlingParserI
        Parameters:
        s - Complex XML element string
        Returns:
        Map with abbreviation of author/source e.g (Qutb) as key and StarlingReference object as value.
